Package: sleepproxyclient
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python-dnspython, avahi-utils, pm-utils, python-argparse, python-netifaces
Description: mDNS Sleep Proxy Client implementation.
 sleepproxyclient is a Linux implementation for Wake On Demand by using
 a Sleep Proxy Server.
 Specified services will be registered by the Sleep Proxy Server before
 going to sleep or hibernation. The client will be woken up by the server
 on accessing on of this services.
 An mDNS announced Sleep Proxy Server (_sleep-proxy._udp) is required on
 the local network to work properly.